[Black "Bishops Before Knights: 6.Qb3"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. c3 Nc6 5. Bd3
{ This is a different move order which allows White to save a tempo on a knight move but develop the bishop to prevent Black from playing ...Bf5. However, this move has its own disadvantages which i will illustrate. }
5... Qb6 { Same idea - to attack the b-pawn. } 6. Qb3 c4
{ This time White has to exchange queens and lose a tempo with a bishop move. }
7. Qxb6 axb6 8. Bc2 b5
{ Black gets a better version of this famous endgame, where their plan is to attack on the queenside with both b-pawns. }
