1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. c3 Qb6 6. b3
{ Definitely not the strongest option. That's why it is mainly played only at the club level.  6.Qb3  ,  6.Qc2  &  6.Qc1  are more common. }
6... cxd4 { The most effective way to prove that this is a mistake. } 7. cxd4
{ This weakens the king, allows checks on b4 and a5 and even ...Nb4 } 7... Nh5
{ 7...Bf5  immediately is a good alternative. } 8. Bg3 Nxg3 9. hxg3 e5
{ And Black brings all their pieces into the game. } 10. dxe5 Bb4+ 11. Nfd2 d4
{ And the white position is ruined. } *

