[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide"]
[Black "5.Nd2 Mainline (Before Nf3): 6.Ngf3, 7.Nh4 "]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nd2 Bf5 6. Ngf3 e6
{ In this position, White has 8 main responses where we have to play very carefully and properly if we want to have a nice and easy position to play. }
7. Nh4 Be4
{ Every time when our opponent plays Nh4, we have to put the bishop on e4 in order to provoke f3, and then the knight on h4 will be a little bit isolated from the game. By the way, we can see a similar idea in the Slav defense. }
8. f3 Bg6
{ There is a very nice game in this position is between: Zaitsev,A - Potkin,V 2018, 0-1. }
9. g4 { One of the main ideas for White . } 9... Bd6
{ The best move in that position. The idea is to attack his active bishop and to exchange it for our developed bishop. }
10. Bg3 Qc7 { We continue to attack the bishop! } 11. Kf2 O-O 12. Nxg6 fxg6
{ That's the tricky moment when we take the g6-knight with the f-pawn and White's king falls under attack. Our plan is very simple: to open files and diagonals. }
*

