{ Important move! If Black takes on d6, white continues 9. Bxd6 and Black can't castle kingside anymore. If Black tries  8...O-O  White captures  9.dxe7  and continues with 10. Bd6 winning the exchange. }
9. Ng3 O-O 10. Qd2 Nd5
{ A strong tactical strike! Black gets several points to attack. 11. Nxd5 allows Black to get a strong pawn center and weakens the d6-pawn. }
11. Ngxe4 Nxf4 12. Qxf4 a6 { With ...b5 and queenside fianchetto next. } 13.
Bxd7 Bxd7
{ Black has the bishop pair and a weak pawn on d6 to bite on. Therefore, they have better chances in this position. }
14. Nxc5 Rc8 15. Nxd7
{ It's difficult to suggest anything else for White because both knights are under attack. }
15... Qxd7 16. Rd1 Bxc3+ 17. bxc3 Rxc3
{ The pawn can be lost if White loses a tempo. If not, Black continues with ...Rd8 and ...Qc6 pressuring White's pawns on the queenside. }
