4. d5
{ This move reflects the main idea of this variation. White grabs some space in the center and slows down Black's development. }
4... Nf6
{ A natural developing move that forces White to defend the central pawn. } 5.
Nc3 g6
{ There is no need to fight for the e4 pawn. We can sacrifice it back in order to finish development. }
6. Bc4 Bg7 7. Nge2 O-O 8. d6 exd6
{ Maybe not the best, but the most simple continuation that offers clear play and a better position for Black. }
9. Bxd6 Re8 10. Bxc5 Nbd7 { Black develops while gaining tempi. } 11. Bd4 Qc7
12. Bb3 Ne5
{ With strong prospects for a kingside attack. The material is equal, but White can hardly come up with an active plan. They have to defend. }
*

