{ This is the 3rd most popular move in this position. However, some strong Grandmasters recommend it and play this line mainly in blitz. If we just reverse colors, it will be similar to Albin Counter-Gambit, but with the bishop on f4, which sometimes is useless, sometimes not. }
3... dxe4
{ The main move for this position. To refute a gambit you should accept it! However, such moves as @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp2pppp/8/2pp4/3PPB2/8/PPP2PPP/RN1QKBNR b KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Nc6  and  @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp2pppp/8/2pp4/3PPB2/8/PPP2PPP/RN1QKBNR b KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...Nf6  are also playable. For example, Magnus Carlsen played them in some of his online blitz games. }
