{ A natural developing move that forces White to defend the central pawn. } 5.
Nc3 g6
{ There is no need to fight for the e4 pawn. We can sacrifice it back in order to finish development. }
6. Qd2 Bg7 7. f3
{ A sharp continuation where Black has to defend and keep their extra pawn. 6. f3 leads to similar lines. }
7... exf3 { Otherwise, White gets another pawn in the center. } 8. Nxf3 Nbd7 9.
O-O-O { Planning for a kingside attack. } 9... O-O 10. d6 exd6
{ 10...e6  is a good alternative according to the engines, but it's better to open the position to avoid a strong kingside attack from White. }
