7. O-O O-O 8. Nc3 Nh5 { Another way to control the e5 square. } 9. Bg5 Be7 10.
Bxe7 Qxe7 { With the idea ...Rd8, ...e5, ...h6. } 11. e4
{ The only counterplay for White. } 11... dxe4 12. Bxe4 Rd8
{ The most logical move - to put the rook on the open file with a tempo. } 13.
Qe2 Bd7
{ The plan for Black is to play: ...Nf4 @@StartBracket@@or ...Nf6@@EndBracket@@, ...Rac8, ...h6, ...f6!? }
