4... cxd4 { The most competitive move. } 5. exd4 Bf5 6. Bb5
{ Ambitious, but practically leads to all positions favoring Black. } 6... e6
{ In this position, the best set up for Black is: ...Nge7, ...Ng6, ...Bd6, ...O-O, ...Rac8 & ...a6. }
7. a3 { To prevent ...Bb4. } 7... Ne7 8. Nf3 a6
{ Black wants to restrict the light-squared bishop and if White plays Bxc6, Black replaces the knight with the other one. }
9. Be2 Ng6
{ The plan for Black is to play: ...Bd6, ...O-O, ...Rc8, ...h6 & ...Qc7 with better prospects on both sides of the board. }
