{ 9...Bd6  is still possible, but if Black plays for a win, it's better to keep more pieces on the board. }
10. Ne2
{ White's knight doesn't have any prospects on c3. The only thing the knight did was control the e4-square. }
10... O-O 11. c3
{ Creating a pawn chain to make it easier to protect the b2-pawn and cover the b4-square. }
11... Ne4
{ Black centralizes their knight and has a very interesting plan - to play: ...g5, ...a5 @@StartBracket@@preventing white queenside activity@@EndBracket@@ & ...f5 to attack on the kingside. }
