{ To control e5 and threaten ...Qd8-b6. Black also has the option to transpose into a semi-slav via  3...cxd4  . }
4. Nf3 Nf6 5. dxc5 e6
{ If Black captures on c5 with a tempo, the best White may get is an equal position. }
6. b4 { Trying to save the pawn. } 6... a5
{ A typical move to undermine these pawns. } 7. Nd4
{ White tries to exchange the knight on c6 to decrease the pressure on the b4-pawn. }
