3... Nc6
{ To control e5 and threaten ...Qd8-b6. Black also has the option to transpose into a semi-slav via  3...cxd4  . }
4. Nf3 Nf6 5. dxc5 e6
{ If Black captures on c5 with a tempo, the best White may get is an equal position. }
6. b4 { Trying to save the pawn. } 6... a5
{ A typical move to undermine these pawns. } 7. b5
{ The most logical response. } 7... Ne7
{ This position is potentially better for Black. } 8. Nbd2 Ng6
{ A double attack. } 9. Bg3
{ 9.Be3  fails to  9...Ng4  and 10...e5 after that. } 9... Bxc5 10. e3 O-O
{ The plan for Black is to play: ...b6, ...Bb7, ...Bd6 & ...e5 and dominate in the center. }
