1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 c5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. c3 Qb6 6. Qc2 g6
{ Please notice  6...Bf5  doesn't work. White should avoid  7.Qxf5  when Black, of course, captures the pawn and gains the rook after  7...Qxb2  & 8...Qxa1.   But instead of taking on f5 immediately, White should first play @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/pp2pppp/1qn2n2/2pp1b2/3P1B2/2P1PN2/PPQ2PPP/RN2KB1R w KQkq - 3 7@@EndFEN@@  7.dxc5  attacking the black queen. If  7...Qxc5  the bishop on f5 is hanging while the black queen no longer attacks b2. That's why Black has to capture the queen with  7...Bxc2  8.cxb6  axb6  and White is better, the position is open and they can successfully activate their light-squared bishop. 6...g6 makes more sense. Black wants to fianchetto and also keeps in mind to play ...Bc8-f5 later in the game. }
7. h3
{ the idea of the move h3 is to control the g4-square and after ...Nh5 the bishop on f4 can escape to h2. }
7... Bg7
{ 7...Bf5  doesn't look good. White plays  8.dxc5  Qxc5  and  9.Qb3  and gains a tempo attacking on b7. }
8. Nbd2 O-O
{ There are two plans for White: to castle on the kingside or to exchange the queens and to castle on the queenside. }
9. Be2 { This time White wants to play on the queenside. } 9... cxd4
{ A very important move when our queen is on b6. White had a chance to take dxc5 and then go b4 and a4 to obtain the initiative in the game. }
10. exd4 Nh5
{ Attacking the active bishop and planning to play ...e5 in some moment. } 11.
Be3 f5 { With the idea of ...f4 and to take the bishop on e3. } 12. Nb3
{ To release the bishop. } 12... f4 13. Bc1
{ White's pieces look a little bit passive and that's why Black has to pressure and attack immediately. }
13... a5 14. O-O
{ 14.a4  weakens the knight's position on b3 and Black may continue with  14...Bf5  15.Qd1  White's queen is tied down to the knight on b3. }
14... a4 15. Nbd2 e5
{ Black succeeds in playing ...e5, one of their major plans in London System. }
16. Nxe5 Bxe5 17. dxe5 Bf5 { Black develops their bishop with a tempo. } 18.
Qd1 Ng3 { Another tempo move. } 19. Re1 Nxe5
{ There is no good move with the e2-bishop to create a discovered attack. The plan for Black is to play: ...Nxe2, ...Rae8, ...Nd3 & ...f3 }
