{ Black continues playing on the queenside and intends to create a weakness on c3 or b2 and then attack it. For these purposes, Black should exchange the bishops and activate one of the rooks to the b-file. White’s only logical plan is to open the position in the center with e3-e4. If this happens, Black should exchange on c4, continue their activity on the queenside and even take the game into an endgame. }
