13... cxb3 14. axb3 O-O
{ Of course, before we start our attack we have to secure the king. } 15. O-O
Rfc8
{ Pressuring the c3-pawn and having in mind rook activity down the c-file. }
16. c4 { This move gives a strong point on b4 for a black knight. } 16... Nb4
17. Ne5 a5 { Supporting the knight. } 18. Qb2 Qd8
{ The plan for Black is to play: ...Ne4 @@StartBracket@@or ...Ne8@@EndBracket@@, ...b6 & ...f6 chasing the knight. }
