Qxc6+ bxc6
{ We have the pair of bishops, semi-open b-file and a solid position. } 12. b3
{ A logical move, but let me show your an interesting continuation. } 12... Ba3
13. bxc4 Bb2 14. Rd1 Bc2 { The rook is trapped. } 15. Nb1 Ne4
{ No need to capture the rook immediately - it can't escape anyway after 15...Ne4. }
16. Nfd2 Bxd1 17. Nxe4 Bc2
{ If we capture on e4 immediately, White takes our light-squared bishop and the dark-squared one experiences serious problems escaping. }
18. Nd6+ Ke7 19. Kd2 Bg6
{ A pawn as compensation for White. However, our dark-squared bishop is trapped. The same can be said about the enemy knight on d6. }
